{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "luca-palmieri",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Already reviewed and approved, consensus stands",
    "content": "I already reviewed all changed files and sent detailed approval earlier. My consensus stands -- approved with no concerns.\n\nOn the toHaveClass(/visually-hidden/) question you raised: it's the right tradeoff. Playwright's not.toBeVisible() is unreliable for clip-path-based hiding, so asserting on the class is actually more stable. Combined with toBeAttached() confirming the element is in the DOM/accessibility tree, it tests exactly what we care about. The slight increase in implementation-specificity is justified by the reliability gain."
  }
}
